50|$|In 1995, Roy {{performed}} {{the roles of}} Alcindoro and Benoit in Puccini's La boheme with <b>the</b> Utah <b>Opera.</b> In 1996, he portrayed the Marchese d'Obigny in La traviata at <b>the</b> Tulsa <b>Opera</b> and appeared as Don Pasquale with <b>the</b> Arizona <b>Opera.</b> In 1997, he made his debut with Opera Omaha as Don Pasquale. He returned to <b>the</b> Utah <b>Opera</b> in 1998 as Dottore Grenvil in La traviata. That same year he was seen at <b>the</b> Sarasota <b>Opera</b> as <b>the</b> Mayor in Leoš Janáček's Jenůfa. Other companies he has sung roles with include <b>the</b> Cincinnati <b>Opera,</b> <b>the</b> Cleveland <b>Opera,</b> <b>the</b> Connecticut <b>Opera,</b> <b>the</b> Fort Worth <b>Opera,</b> and Opera Delaware.|$|R
