5000|$|He {{was best}} known as an opera {{conductor}} and led memorable productions at <b>the</b> Hamburg State <b>Opera,</b> <b>the</b> Deutsche Oper Berlin, <b>the</b> Bavarian State <b>Opera,</b> <b>the</b> Rome <b>Opera,</b> <b>the</b> Frankfurt <b>Opera,</b> <b>the</b> Monte Carlo <b>Opera</b> and <b>the</b> Bastille <b>Opera</b> in Paris. He also conducted in 1988 Jean-Pierre Ponnelle's critically acclaimed production of Britten’s “Peter Grimes” at the Maggio Musicale Fiorentino in Italy [...] and in 1992 Ruth Berghaus’ famous production of Strauss’ “Rosenkavalier” in <b>the</b> Frankfurt <b>Opera</b> with Deborah Polaski debuting {{the role of the}} Marschallin.|$|R
